        <div class="framing-tile-eyebrow">The patient North Star</div>
        <div class="framing-tile-h">The system finds him before the symptoms find him.</div>
        <div class="framing-tile-body">Abdul does not feel ill. He has never been to the GP about his heart. The cohort he belongs to — middle-aged men with family-history risk — is exactly the cohort the in-clinic system finds last. <strong>The home pathway finds him first.</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="framing-tile">
        <div class="framing-tile-eyebrow">Why this works for him</div>
        <div class="framing-tile-h">The NHS App is the front door. The kit is the test. The result is in his record.</div>
        <div class="framing-tile-body">No clinic visit to book. No phlebotomist to find a slot with. No half-day off work. <strong>The kit arrives. He takes the sample. The result lands in the system he already uses for everything else.</strong></div>
